# AuraPredict — North Star for Development

## How to Build

### Prerequisites
- Node.js 20+, npm
- Copy `.env.example` → `.env` and fill in required keys (see Key ENV Vars below)

### Daily dev
```
npm install          # first time
npm run dev          # Vite dev server → http://127.0.0.1:5173
npm run indexer      # run local indexer (separate terminal)
```

### Verify before committing
```
npx tsc --noEmit     # TypeScript — must be clean (zero errors)
npx vite build       # production build — must succeed
```

### Contracts
```
npm run compile              # compile Hardhat contracts
npm test                     # Hardhat unit tests
npm run deploy:arc:v5        # deploy V5 contract to Arc Testnet
npm run abi:v5               # regenerate ABI after contract changes
```

### Other scripts
```
npm run indexer:once         # one-shot indexer run (CI/staging)
npm run oracle:backtest      # backtest oracle resolution logic
npm run smoke:api            # smoke-test production API endpoints
npm run test:e2e             # Playwright end-to-end tests
```

### Key ENV Vars
| Var | What it does |
|---|---|
| `VITE_AURAPREDICT_V5_ADDRESS` | On-chain contract address |
| `VITE_AURA_INDEXER_URL` | Local indexer URL (default: http://127.0.0.1:8787) |
| `VITE_WALLETCONNECT_PROJECT_ID` | WalletConnect — required for wallet modal |
| `VITE_MAGIC_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` | Magic.link — required for email login |
| `GEMINI_API_KEY` / `OPENAI_API_KEY` | AI resolution oracle |
| `PRIVATE_KEY` | Deployer wallet private key (never commit) |
| `AURA_RESOLUTION_ADMIN_TOKEN` | Auth for resolution API |

